# Git Branching

- Primary branch flow MUST be `main <- dev <- feature/*` and `main <- dev <- vibe/*`.
- Issue-based work MUST be done on a feature branch created from `dev`.
- Exploratory work MUST be done on a vibe branch created from `dev`.
- Normal code changes MUST NOT be made directly on `main`.
- Normal code changes MUST NOT be made directly on `dev` unless the user explicitly allows it.
- Before creating a branch from `dev`, `dev` MUST be synced with remote `dev`.
- Issue-based feature branches MUST include the issue number and a short slug.
- Vibe branches MUST use the `vibe/` prefix.
